This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with sentiment analysis in social media, which is a common topic in natural language processing research. It may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves analyzing sentiment in social media. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as sentiment analysis can be seen as a form of information retrieval. Machine Learning (cs.LG) is also a possibility as many approaches to sentiment analysis involve machine learning techniques. Finally, Cybersecurity (cs.CY) is a less likely possibility as sentiment analysis can be used in cybersecurity applications, such as detecting malicious intent in social media posts.
